returns._0: bool                    Whether enough time has passed since the last deposit for the user to be ale to withdraw

claimRewards().details: Can only be called by the owner of the vault

deposit(uint256,uint256).details: Can only be called by the owner of the vault

params.amount_: The amount of pair tokens to deposit
params.minLpAmount_: The minimum acceptable amount of LP tokens to receive back

returns.lpAmountOut: The amount of LP tokens received by the transaction

emergencyWithdraw(uint256,uint256[]).details: Can only be called by the owner of the vault. Can only be called when the vault is paused

params.lpAmount_: The amount of LP tokens to withdraw from Balancer
params.minTokenAmounts_: The minimum acceptable amounts of OHM (first entry), and pair tokens (second entry) to receive back from Balancer

returns._0: uint256                 The amount of OHM received
returns._1: uint256                 The amount of pair tokens received

returns._0: uint256                 LP balance deposited into Aura
RewardsData[]           The vault's unclaimed rewards in Aura

withdraw(uint256,uint256[],uint256,bool).details: Can only be called by the owner of the vault

params.claim_: Whether to claim outstanding rewards from Aura
params.lpAmount_: The amount of LP tokens to withdraw from Balancer
params.minTokenAmountUser_: The minimum acceptable amount of pair tokens to receive back from the vault
params.minTokenAmountsBalancer_: The minimum acceptable amounts of OHM (first entry), and pair tokens (second entry) to receive back from Balancer

returns._0: uint256                 The amount of OHM received
returns._1: uint256                 The amount of pair tokens received

canWithdraw().notice: Gets whether enough time has passed since the last deposit for the user to be ale to withdraw

deposit(uint256,uint256).notice: Mints OHM against a pair token deposit and uses the OHM and pair tokens to add liquidity to a Balancer pool

emergencyWithdraw(uint256,uint256[]).notice: Withdraws LP tokens from Aura and Balancer, returns the pair tokens to the user

getLpBalance().notice: Gets the LP balance of the contract based on its deposits to Aura

getOutstandingRewards().notice: Returns the vault's unclaimed rewards in Aura

getUserPairShare().notice: Gets the contract's claim on pair tokens based on its LP balance deposited into Aura

lastDeposit().notice: The last timestamp a deposit was made. Used for enforcing minimum deposit lengths.

withdraw(uint256,uint256[],uint256,bool).notice: Withdraws LP tokens from Aura and Balancer, burns the OHM side, and returns the pair token side to the user
